\fs24 \cf0 Prioritize dialect accessibility.
\f1\b0  Given that Pioneer and Merdeka generation seniors often speak dialects rather than Mandarin, training should include basic Hokkien, Teochew, and Cantonese phrases at minimum. Consider dialect-specific audio versions of key content, and develop a quick reference card with essential phrases across languages.\

\f0\b Build in extensive scenario practice.
\f1\b0  Adult learning research confirms that realistic, job-relevant scenarios with branching consequences produce better skill transfer than information-only content. Each module should include at least one decision-point scenario requiring application of learned skills.\

\f0\b Create accessible job aids.
\f1\b0  Beyond the e-learning modules, provide downloadable quick reference guides: a laminated scheme eligibility summary card, a home safety observation checklist, an escalation decision tree, and a communication adaptations reminder card. These support just-in-time learning during actual PHVs.\

